een the\nadjacent quantized plateaus change with the topological charge for both of the\nabove cases. The momentum-integrated three-dimensional Hall conductivity is not\nquantized; however, it bears the signature of chiral LLs as resulting in the\nlinear dependence on $\\mu$ for small $\\mu$. The linear zone (its slope) reduces\n(increases) as the tilt (topological charge) of the underlying WSM increases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Feb 2022 11:48:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 31 Jul 2022 06:37:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-02"}
